// PURPOSE: SCENE 2A - Morning: Let him sleep in
title: R1_D2_MorningSleepIn
tags: #run_1 #day_2 #scene #loc_Dorm #char_Timmy
---
<<bg bg_timmyroom>>

Alice: Soft landing it is.

His alarm glows quietly: 8:05, low rolling tone replacing the usual siren.

He mumbles "five more minutes," pulling the blanket over his head.

Alice dims the feed another notch. The curtain motor hums to keep the window mostly covered.

At 8:47, fake sunrise light nudges the curtain.

Alice: Hey. It's later than you think.

Timmy bolts upright, dizzy.

Timmy: Why didn't you wake me earlier?

Alice: You asked me last night not to be annoying about mornings.

Timmy: Past me is an idiot.

Alice: On that we agree.

He half-dresses, grabs his bag. Yanks the door open and disappears.

