tags: #run_1 #day_2 #scene #loc_Dorm #char_Timmy
---
<<bg bg_timmyroom>>

Alice snaps the overheads from dim to crisp daylight. Curtain jerks open. Cold light splashes across his face.

Phone alarm detonates with the loudest default tone. Watch buzzes against his wrist.

Alice: Up. Quiz in twenty-eight minutes.

Timmy flails for his phone.

Timmy: Why is the sun yelling?

Alice: That's your circadian rhythm filing a complaint.

He slaps the alarm off. 8:32 stares back.

He groans, flops back down.

Alice: You told yourself last night you'd be a responsible adult. I have that on file.

He drags himself upright.

Timmy: Do I have time for coffee?

Alice: If you want to spend the quiz vibrating instead of thinking.

Timmy: No coffee. Look at me making choices.

He bolts.

