// PURPOSE: SCENE 3A - Quiz: MISSED
title: R1_D2_Quiz_Missed
tags: #run_1 #day_2 #scene #loc_Campus #char_Timmy
---
<<bg bg_hallway>>
<<set $r1_d2_quiz_result = "missed">>

The clock on his phone reads 9:07 when Timmy finally jolts awake. He stares at the ceiling for two seconds. Then his whole body goes rigid.

Timmy: No. No no no—

He's moving before he's thinking, shoving feet into shoes that may or may not match, grabbing his backpack without checking if anything useful is inside.

Alice: Heart rate just doubled. Full panic mode.

The hallway blurs. Stairs taken two at a time. His lungs burn by the time he reaches the building.

Clock over the door: 9:11.

Through the small window, students are bent over papers. Pencils scratching. The quiet, focused energy of people who showed up on time.

And there, two rows from the front, a girl with dark hair, focused posture. Writing steadily without looking up.

Timmy stops. Stares at her through the glass. His hand reaches for the door handle, then freezes.

Alice: He's been standing there for fifteen seconds. He's not going in.

Inside, the professor glances toward the window. That brief, disappointed teacher look.

Timmy's hand drops. He takes a step back. Then another. Then he's retreating down the hall, finding a bench in a quiet corner.

He pulls out his phone. Opens his email. Types: "Professor, I'm so sorry, I woke up with food poisoning and—"

He stops. Deletes it. Types again. Deletes again.

Alice: He's been editing that email for four minutes. He hasn't sent anything.

He closes the email app. Opens a game instead.

<<set $sanity -= 3>>
<<jump R1_D2_PostQuiz>>
===

// PURPOSE: SCENE 3B - Quiz: STRUGGLED
title: R1_D2_Quiz_Struggled
tags: #run_1 #day_2 #scene #loc_Classroom #char_Timmy
---
<<bg bg_classroom>>
<<set $r1_d2_quiz_result = "struggled">>

Timmy crashes into a seat at 8:59, chest heaving, barely conscious.

Alice: Heart rate elevated. Blood pressure high. Cognitive function... we'll see.

The quiz lands on his desk. He stares at the first question. His pen hovers.

Define "price elasticity of demand."

He writes something. Crosses it out. Writes something else. Crosses that out too.

Two rows ahead, Charlotte writes without hesitation. Timmy's eyes drift toward her paper. His head tilts slightly.

Alice: He's looking at her answers.

His neck flushes red. He jerks his gaze back to his own paper, jaw tight.

Alice: He's not going to cheat. But he thought about it.

He hunches over his quiz, one arm curled around it like a shield.

<<if $r1_d1_strategy == "study_adjacent">>
He pauses. Mouths something silently—looks like "supply... demand... raccoon?" Writes faster.

Alice: Something from last night stuck. He's pulling fragments.
<<else>>
He's guessing. You can tell by the way he doesn't pause between questions—just writes whatever comes first and moves on.

Alice: That's not strategy. That's surrender.
<<endif>>

Charlotte finishes. Walks to the front. Passes Timmy's desk. He doesn't look up, but his pen stops moving until she's gone.

<<set $sanity -= 1>>
<<jump R1_D2_PostQuiz>>
===

// PURPOSE: SCENE 3C - Quiz: OKAY
title: R1_D2_Quiz_Okay
tags: #run_1 #day_2 #scene #loc_Classroom #char_Timmy
---
<<bg bg_classroom>>
<<set $r1_d2_quiz_result = "okay">>

Timmy slides into his seat at 8:58. Tired, but upright.

Alice: Baseline stable. He might actually function today.

He reads the first question. His eyebrows lift slightly. He starts writing.

Alice: He knows that one.

Question two. He pauses, taps his pen against his lip. Circles back to it. Keeps moving.

Two rows ahead, Charlotte finishes early. She stands, collects her bag, walks toward the front to turn in her paper.

Timmy watches her approach out of his peripheral vision. As she passes his desk, he fumbles his pen. It clatters against the desk, then the floor, then rolls under the seat of the person next to him.

Alice: Smooth.

He retrieves it, face red, not looking at anyone. Charlotte's already gone.

He finishes the quiz. Hands it in. Walks out.

Timmy: Not a disaster. That's something.

<<set $sanity += 1>>
