// PURPOSE: Office Hours - Push path
title: R1_D2_Task_OfficeHours_Push
tags: #run_1 #day_2 #dayplanner #char_Alice #loc_Dorm
---
<<bg bg_timmyroom>>

Alice: Strong-arming it is.

Cut to: Timmy walking into the professor's office. His body language radiates discomfort. Shoulders hunched, backpack clutched like a shield.

The professor doesn't look up from his laptop.

Professor: Name?

Timmy: Uh. Tim. Timothy. Kowalski.

Professor: Kowalski. Quiz scores.

He types something. The keyboard sounds like judgment.

Professor: You're behind.

Timmy: I know. I'm trying to—

Professor: Have a seat.

Timmy sits on the edge of the chair, knees together, like he's waiting in the principal's office.

The professor finally looks up. Peers over his glasses. The look isn't mean. It's worse. It's the look of someone who has had this conversation four hundred times.

Professor: What happened?

Timmy: I don't... I studied. Kind of. I thought I knew it.

Professor: But you didn't.

Timmy: No. I guess not.

Silence. The professor waits. Timmy shifts in his seat.

Timmy: Is there anything I can do? To bring my grade up?

Professor: There's the next quiz. There's the midterm. There's the final. Those are the things you can do.

Timmy: Right. Okay.

Professor: Office hours are Tuesdays and Thursdays. Bring specific questions. Not "I don't understand." Specific.

Timmy: Okay.

Professor: Is there anything else?

There's nothing else. Timmy was hoping for something, guidance maybe, or acknowledgment that he's a person and not just a data point. But the professor is already looking at his laptop again.

Timmy: No. Thanks.

He leaves. The door clicks shut behind him.

Cut back to: Your console.

Alice: He hated every second. But he went.

Player: Is that good?

Alice: It's forward motion. Forward motion beats spiraling in place.

<<set $officehours_status = "pushed">>
<<set $sanity += 2>>
<<set $engagement += 1>>
<<jump R1_D2_Dayplanner>>
